WEBVTT

00:03.796 --> 00:05.463
How do you do?

00:08.384 --> 00:11.010
Mr. Carl Laemmle feels
it would be a little unkind

00:11.095 --> 00:15.098
to present this picture
without just a word
of friendly warning.

00:15.724 --> 00:18.893
We are about to unfold
the story of Frankenstein,

00:19.395 --> 00:21.062
a man of science,

00:21.438 --> 00:24.440
who sought to create
a man after his own image

00:25.234 --> 00:27.735
without reckoning upon God.

00:29.279 --> 00:32.240
lt is one of
the strangest tales ever told.

00:33.158 --> 00:36.452
lt deals with the two great
mysteries of creation,

00:36.578 --> 00:38.579
life and death.

00:40.165 --> 00:42.208
l think it will thrill you.

00:42.292 --> 00:44.001
lt may shock you.

00:45.003 --> 00:47.338
lt might even horrify you.

00:48.465 --> 00:53.136
So, if any of you feel that
you do not care to subject
your nerves to such a strain,

00:53.262 --> 00:55.638
now is your chance to. . .

00:55.764 --> 00:58.433
Well, we've warned you.

02:03.582 --> 02:05.583
(PRlEST PRAYlNG lN LATlN)

02:07.878 --> 02:09.628
(BELL TOLLlNG)
(CRYlNG)

02:10.047 --> 02:11.088
PRlEST: Amen.

02:11.590 --> 02:12.590
(BELL CONTlNUES)

02:18.180 --> 02:19.472
(CRYlNG CONTlNUES)

02:37.366 --> 02:40.076
Down ! Down, you fool !

03:21.994 --> 03:23.452
(DlRT THUDDlNG)

04:13.670 --> 04:14.712
Now.

04:15.422 --> 04:16.714
Come on.

04:20.761 --> 04:22.219
Hurry, hurry.

04:24.806 --> 04:26.098
(BELL CONTlNUES TOLLlNG)

04:35.776 --> 04:36.776
(BELL STOPS)

04:41.740 --> 04:44.700
The moon's rising.
We've no time to lose.

04:44.826 --> 04:45.826
(CLATTERlNG)

04:45.911 --> 04:47.161
Oh, careful !

04:53.877 --> 04:55.211
There we go.

04:55.337 --> 04:56.754
Here he comes!

05:06.598 --> 05:09.892
He's just resting, waiting
for a new life to come.

05:22.823 --> 05:24.365
(WOOD CREAKlNG)

05:25.826 --> 05:27.118
(BOTH GRUNTlNG)

05:33.542 --> 05:34.959
Here we are.

05:38.880 --> 05:40.256
(DOG BARKlNG)

05:41.758 --> 05:44.969
Look. lt's still here.

05:47.431 --> 05:49.473
Climb up and cut the rope.

05:49.933 --> 05:51.100
No!

05:51.184 --> 05:53.102
Go on. lt can't hurt you.

05:54.104 --> 05:55.604
Here's the knife.

06:03.196 --> 06:04.363
(BARKlNG CONTlNUES)

06:07.117 --> 06:08.117
(PANTlNG)

06:18.795 --> 06:20.129
Look out!

06:22.257 --> 06:23.841
Here's the knife.

06:24.468 --> 06:25.926
Here l come.

06:29.973 --> 06:31.474
ls it all right?

06:32.017 --> 06:33.684
The neck's broken.

06:33.977 --> 06:35.811
The brain is useless.

06:36.605 --> 06:38.689
We must find another brain.

06:48.158 --> 06:49.825
That will do,
gentlemen.

