the most perfect specimens
of the human brain

07:17.229 --> 07:19.355
that has ever come
to my attention
at the university.

07:19.439 --> 07:22.858
And here, the abnormal brain
of the typical criminal.

07:23.360 --> 07:28.114
Observe, ladies and gentlemen,
the scarcity of convolutions
on the frontal lobe,

07:28.365 --> 07:31.033
as compared to that of
the normal brain,

07:31.535 --> 07:35.412
and the distinct degeneration
of the middle frontal lobe.

07:36.206 --> 07:38.541
All of these
degenerate characteristics

07:38.625 --> 07:41.752
check amazingly
with the case history of
the dead man before us,

07:41.878 --> 07:46.549
whose life was
one of brutality,
of violence and murder.

07:47.217 --> 07:50.094
Both of these jars
will remain here for
your further inspection.

07:50.220 --> 07:52.388
Thank you, gentlemen.
The class is dismissed.

07:55.392 --> 07:57.226
(TALKlNG lNDlSTlNCTLY)

08:43.648 --> 08:44.982
(EXCLAlMS FEARFULLY)

08:56.036 --> 08:57.411
(GONG BANGS)

09:28.360 --> 09:30.152
Herr Victor Moritz.

09:33.823 --> 09:35.032
Victor.

09:35.659 --> 09:37.034
l'm so glad
you've come.

09:37.118 --> 09:38.160
What is it, Elizabeth?

09:38.245 --> 09:39.245
Oh, you've heard
from Henry.

09:39.329 --> 09:41.705
Yes. The first word
in four months.

09:41.831 --> 09:43.332
lt just came.

09:44.334 --> 09:45.668
Victor, you must help me.

09:45.752 --> 09:47.544
Why, of course
l'll help you.

09:48.838 --> 09:50.172
l'm afraid.

09:50.548 --> 09:53.634
l've read this over
and over again,
but they're just words

09:53.718 --> 09:55.678
that l can't understand.

09:56.137 --> 09:57.346
Listen.

09:57.681 --> 10:00.516
"You must have faith in me,
Elizabeth. Wait.

10:00.642 --> 10:03.686
"My work must come first,
even before you.

10:03.812 --> 10:06.438
"At night, the winds howl
in the mountains.

10:06.523 --> 10:08.691
"There is no one here.

10:08.817 --> 10:11.527
"Prying eyes can't peer
into my secret."

10:12.028 --> 10:13.153
What can he mean?

10:13.655 --> 10:14.738
What does he say then?

10:17.033 --> 10:19.326
"l am living in an abandoned,
old watchtower,

10:19.411 --> 10:21.495
"close to the town
of Goldstadt.

10:21.579 --> 10:24.999
"Only my assistant is here
to help me
with my experiments."

10:25.417 --> 10:26.875
Oh, his experiments.

10:27.377 --> 10:29.044
Yes, that's what
frightens me.

10:29.379 --> 10:33.132
The very day we announced
our engagement,
he told me of his experiments.

10:33.216 --> 10:35.634
He said he was on the verge
of a discovery so terrific

10:35.719 --> 10:37.720
that he doubted
his own sanity.

10:38.054 --> 10:41.682
There was a strange look
in his eyes, some mystery.

10:42.017 --> 10:44.393
His words carried me
right away.

10:45.061 --> 10:47.479
Of course, l've never
doubted him,
but still l worry.

10:47.564 --> 10:48.605
l can't help it.

10:49.441 --> 10:51.233
And now this letter.

10:51.359 --> 10:54.069
All this uncertainty
can't go on. l must know.

10:54.195 --> 10:56.530
Victor, have you seen him?

10:56.614 --> 10:59.241
Yes. About three weeks ago.

10:59.367 --> 11:01.327
l met him walking alone
in the woods.

11:01.411 --> 11:02.953
He spoke to me
of his work, too.

11:03.079 --> 11:05.581
l asked him if l might
visit his laboratory.

11:05.707 --> 11:08.709
He just glared at me
and said he would let
no one go there.

11:08.793 --> 11:10.461
His manner was very strange.

11:10.587 --> 11:12.254
Oh, what can we do?

11:12.756 --> 11:14.048
Oh, if he should be ill. . .

11:14.132 --> 11:15.341
Now, don't worry.

11:15.425 --> 11:18.844
l'll go to Dr. Waldman,
Henry's old professor
in medical school.

11:18.928 --> 11:21.430
Perhaps he can tell me
more about all this.

11:21.556 --> 11:23.599
Oh, Victor, you're a dear.

11:23.725 --> 11:26.101
You know l'd go
to the ends of
the Earth for you.

11:26.227 --> 11:29.438
l shouldn't like that.
l'm far too fond of you.

11:29.606 --> 11:30.981
l wish you were.

11:33.443 --> 11:34.401
Victor.

11:34.486 --> 11:35.611
l'm sorry.

11:40.283 --> 11:42.785
Good night, Victor,
and thank you. Thank you.

11:42.911 --> 11:46.121
Good night.
And don't worry. Promise?

11:46.623 --> 11:47.790
l won't.

11:53.338 --> 11:55.422
Victor?
What is it?

11:57.592 --> 11:58.550
l'm coming with you.

11:58.635 --> 11:59.760
But, Elizabeth,
you can't do that!

11:59.844 --> 12:02.304
l must! l'll be
ready in a minute.

12:07.143 --> 12:10.020
Herr Frankenstein
is a most brilliant
young man,

12:10.146 --> 12:12.981
yet so erratic,
he troubles me.

12:13.817 --> 12:17.444
l'm worried about Henry.
Why has he left
the university?

12:17.779 --> 12:21.782
He was doing so well,
and he seemed
so happy with his work.

12:22.659 --> 12:24.451
Well, you know,
his researches
in the field of

12:24.536 --> 12:26.787
chemical galvanism
and electro-biology

12:26.871 --> 12:30.290
were far in advance
of our theories here
at the university.

12:30.792 --> 12:33.502
ln fact, they had reached
a most advanced stage.

12:33.628 --> 12:35.796
