24:50.281 --> 24:52.782
Look. lt's moving.

24:53.784 --> 24:56.953
lt's alive. lt's alive.

24:58.289 --> 24:59.747
lt's alive.

24:59.874 --> 25:01.958
lt's moving.
lt's alive.

25:02.293 --> 25:06.004
Oh, it's alive!
lt's alive! lt's alive!

25:06.088 --> 25:07.380
lt's alive!

25:07.464 --> 25:08.798
Henry,
in the name of God.

25:08.924 --> 25:10.425
ln the name of God !

25:10.551 --> 25:13.636
Now l know what
it feels like to be God !

25:14.180 --> 25:15.722
(THUNDER CONTlNUES)

25:25.649 --> 25:27.817
Henry is well,
but he's very busy.

25:27.943 --> 25:30.111
He said he would
get in touch
with you soon.

25:30.237 --> 25:32.155
Don't worry
about him, Baron.

25:32.239 --> 25:33.656
He'll be home
in a few days.

25:34.241 --> 25:37.076
You two have it
all arranged,
haven't you?

25:37.286 --> 25:39.329
You think l'm an idiot,
don't you?

25:39.455 --> 25:40.788
But l'm not.

25:41.832 --> 25:43.708
Anyone can see
with half an eye

25:43.792 --> 25:45.210
that there's
something wrong.

25:45.294 --> 25:48.379
And l have two eyes,
pretty good ones, at that.

25:48.464 --> 25:49.547
Well, what is it?

25:49.632 --> 25:51.466
You're quite
mistaken, Baron.

25:51.592 --> 25:54.302
What's the matter
with my son?
What's he doing?

25:54.595 --> 25:56.846
He's completing
his experiments,
that's all.

25:56.972 --> 26:00.016
Why does he go messing around
an old, ruined windmill,

26:00.142 --> 26:02.894
when he has a decent
house, a bath,

26:02.978 --> 26:06.856
good food and drink
and a darned pretty girl
to come back to?

26:07.024 --> 26:08.691
(SCOFFS)
Will you tell me that?

26:09.151 --> 26:10.485
Oh, Baron,
you don't understand.

26:10.569 --> 26:12.612
l understand
perfectly well.

26:12.821 --> 26:16.157
There's another woman,
and you're afraid
to tell me.

26:16.283 --> 26:19.160
Pretty sort of
experiments
these must be.

26:19.286 --> 26:20.578
Oh, but you're wrong.

26:20.663 --> 26:22.538
And how do you know?

26:22.665 --> 26:25.250
lf you please,
Herr Baron,
the Burgomaster.

26:25.334 --> 26:27.627
Well, tell him
to go away.

26:27.711 --> 26:29.170
But he says
it's important.

26:29.296 --> 26:33.174
Nothing the Burgomaster
can say can be of
the slightest importance.

26:34.843 --> 26:37.720
Good day,
Herr Baron. FrÃ¤ulein.

26:38.055 --> 26:39.973
Well, what do you want?

26:40.182 --> 26:43.059
lf it's trouble, go away.
l have trouble enough.

26:43.185 --> 26:44.769
Oh, there's
no trouble, sir.

26:44.853 --> 26:48.356
What do you mean,
"No trouble"?
There's nothing but trouble.

26:48.649 --> 26:50.483
l brought you
these flowers.

26:50.859 --> 26:52.485
Thank you, Herr Vogel.

26:53.195 --> 26:56.739
Both in my private
and official capacities
as Burgomaster. . .

26:56.865 --> 27:00.243
Yes, yes, yes, yes,
we know all about that,
but what do you want?

27:00.369 --> 27:02.620
Well, what l really
want to know is,

27:02.705 --> 27:05.123
when will the wedding be,
if you please?

27:05.207 --> 27:07.417
Unless Henry
comes to his senses,

27:07.501 --> 27:09.252
there'll be
no wedding at all.

27:09.545 --> 27:12.088
But, Herr Baron,
the village
is already prepared !

27:12.214 --> 27:13.923
Well, tell them
to unprepare.

27:14.049 --> 27:16.551
Oh, but such
a lovely bride.

27:16.677 --> 27:19.637
Such a fine young man,
the very image
of his father.

27:19.722 --> 27:20.930
Heaven forbid.

27:21.015 --> 27:22.890
But, sir,
everything is ready!

27:22.975 --> 27:26.269
l know that.
Don't keep on
saying so, you idiot.

27:26.353 --> 27:28.604
There's nothing
to cry about.

27:29.106 --> 27:30.857
Good day,
Miss Elizabeth.
(COUGHS)

27:30.941 --> 27:32.817
Good day,
Herr Moritz.

27:32.901 --> 27:34.402
Good day, Herr Vogel.

27:36.238 --> 27:38.072
Good day, Herr Baron.

27:39.199 --> 27:41.200
And good riddance
to you.

27:41.744 --> 27:44.954
There you are.
You see how it is.

27:45.080 --> 27:47.206
The whole village
is kept waiting.

27:47.291 --> 27:49.292
The bride is
kept waiting.

27:49.418 --> 27:51.919
And l am kept waiting.

27:52.129 --> 27:54.630
Henry must come home,
if l have to
fetch him myself.

27:54.757 --> 27:56.424
No, no, Baron.
What do you mean,
"No, no"?

27:56.508 --> 27:57.508
What about his work?

27:57.593 --> 27:59.469
Stuff and nonsense!
What about his wedding?

28:00.095 --> 28:01.929
There is another woman,

28:02.931 --> 28:04.974
and l'm going to find her.

28:11.565 --> 28:12.774
(SlGHS)

28:17.237 --> 28:19.614
Oh, come
and sit down, Doctor.

28:20.449 --> 28:21.991
You must be patient.

28:22.659 --> 28:24.786
Do you expect
perfection at once?

28:25.412 --> 28:28.748
This creature
of yours should be
kept under guard !

28:28.957 --> 28:31.626
Mark my words,
he will prove dangerous!

28:32.961 --> 28:34.337
Dangerous?

28:35.255 --> 28:36.839
Poor old Waldman.

28:40.344 --> 28:43.846
Have you never wanted
to do anything
that was dangerous?

28:44.181 --> 28:47.809
Where should we be
if nobody tried to
find out what lies beyond?

28:48.477 --> 28:52.313
Have you never wanted
to look beyond
the clouds and the stars,

28:52.439 --> 28:55.149
or to know what causes
the trees to bud,

28:55.526 --> 28:58.319
and what changes
a darkness into light?

29:00.989 --> 29:04.659
But if you talk like that,
people call you crazy.

29:07.371 --> 29:10.665
Well, if l could discover
just one of these things,

29:11.333 --> 29:13.543
what eternity is, for example,

29:14.294 --> 29:18.047
l wouldn't care
if they did think
l was crazy!

29:18.632 --> 29:22.135
You're young, my friend.
Your success
has intoxicated you.

29:22.469 --> 29:25.138
Wake up and
look facts in the face.

29:26.348 --> 29:28.850
Here we have a fiend
whose brain. . .

29:28.934 --> 29:31.310
Whose brain must be
given time to develop.

29:32.020 --> 29:34.522
lt's a perfectly
good brain, Doctor.

29:34.857 --> 29:38.484
Well, you ought to know.
lt came from
your own laboratory.

29:39.194 --> 29:43.698
The brain that was
stolen from my laboratory
was a criminal brain.

29:53.041 --> 29:56.711
Oh, well. After all,
it's only a piece of
dead tissue.

29:57.087 --> 29:59.088
Only evil can come of it.

29:59.548 --> 30:02.592
Your health will be
ruined if you persist
in this madness.

30:02.718 --> 30:05.011
l'm astonishingly
sane, Doctor.

30:05.554 --> 30:08.890
You have created a monster,
and it will destroy you !

30:09.057 --> 30:10.850
Patience, patience.

30:11.727 --> 30:14.562
l believe in this monster,
as you call it,

30:14.938 --> 30:17.690
and if you don't, well,
you must leave me alone.

30:17.900 --> 30:20.401
But think of Elizabeth,
your father.

30:20.611 --> 30:22.612
Elizabeth believes in me.

30:22.905 --> 30:25.781
My father never
believes in anyone.

30:27.951 --> 30:30.286
l've got to
experiment further.

30:30.746 --> 30:33.247
He's only a few days old,
remember.

30:33.415 --> 30:36.292
So far he's been kept
in complete darkness.

30:36.919 --> 30:39.545
Wait till l bring him
into the light.

30:39.838 --> 30:41.130
(SLOW FOOTSTEPS)

30:45.260 --> 30:46.761
Here he comes.

30:46.970 --> 30:48.804
Let's turn out the light.

30:52.017 --> 30:53.935
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHlNG)

31:26.927 --> 31:28.135
Come in.

31:29.680 --> 31:30.972
Come in !

31:51.994 --> 31:53.286
Sit down.

31:54.329 --> 31:55.621
Sit down !

32:02.337 --> 32:04.338
You see? lt understands.

32:05.424 --> 32:06.591
Watch.

32:50.218 --> 32:52.595
WALDMAN: Take care,
Herr Frankenstein ! Take care!

32:57.267 --> 32:59.060
Shut out the light!

33:17.245 --> 33:18.496
Sit down.

33:21.083 --> 33:22.750
Go and sit down.

33:41.978 --> 33:43.979
lt understands this time.
lt's wonderful.

33:44.106 --> 33:46.774
Frankenstein ! Frankenstein !
Where is it? Where is it?

33:46.858 --> 33:47.900
(SCREAMS)

33:47.984 --> 33:49.360
Quiet, you fool !

33:50.278 --> 33:51.612
(MUFFLED SCREAM)

33:52.948 --> 33:54.949
Get away with that torch !

33:58.120 --> 33:59.286
(MUFFLED GROWL)

34:01.998 --> 34:03.249
(SNARLlNG)

34:10.465 --> 34:11.632
Quick!

34:12.300 --> 34:14.176
Fetch the rope. Quick!

34:14.678 --> 34:16.137
Stop kicking !

34:16.638 --> 34:18.347
Get him to the cellar!

34:18.473 --> 34:20.306
Shoot it!
lt's a monster!

34:22.476 --> 34:23.518
(CHAlNS RATTLlNG)

34:23.603 --> 34:24.812
(MONSTER HOWLlNG)

34:28.315 --> 34:29.650
(GRUNTlNG)

34:34.197 --> 34:36.489
Quiet. Quiet!

34:41.246 --> 34:42.246
Cooperate!

34:42.330 --> 34:44.206
You'll have the whole
countryside on us!

34:44.666 --> 34:47.208
Come away!
He has the strength
of 1 0 men.

34:48.210 --> 34:50.713
This is madness.
Give me that.

34:51.297 --> 34:52.297
(GROANS)

34:52.716 --> 34:54.550
Oh, come away, Fritz.

34:55.051 --> 34:58.345
Leave it alone.
Leave it alone.

35:06.188 --> 35:07.229
(GROANlNG)

35:23.538 --> 35:25.164
(SCREAMlNG)

35:26.958 --> 35:29.376
Listen. What's that?
Who's there?

35:34.174 --> 35:35.216
(SCREAMlNG CONTlNUES)

35:35.300 --> 35:36.717
lt's Fritz!

35:41.890 --> 35:43.098
(MONSTER GROWLlNG)

35:44.810 --> 35:47.061
Come on, Doctor.
Quick. Hurry.

35:54.110 --> 35:55.402
Get back.

35:56.863 --> 35:57.863
(SNARLS)

35:57.948 --> 35:59.782
Get back.
Get back.

35:59.908 --> 36:01.450
Quick. Quick!

36:04.496 --> 36:05.830
(SNARLlNG)

36:08.667 --> 36:10.000
(GROWLlNG)

36:15.090 --> 36:16.423
(CONTlNUES GROWLlNG)

36:16.925 --> 36:18.342
(POUNDlNG ON DOOR)

36:24.766 --> 36:27.810
He hated Fritz.
Fritz always
tormented him.

36:31.439 --> 36:33.399
Come, come.
Pull yourself together.

36:33.483 --> 36:34.650
What can we do?

36:34.734 --> 36:37.069
Kill it, as you would
any savage animal.

36:37.153 --> 36:40.322
We must overpower him first.
Get me a hypodermic needle.

36:40.448 --> 36:42.157
lt's murder.
lt's our only chance.

36:42.284 --> 36:44.034
ln a few minutes
he'll be through
that door.

36:44.119 --> 36:45.494
Come quick. Hurry.

36:48.456 --> 36:49.665
(POUNDlNG ON DOOR)

36:52.335 --> 36:53.627
(SNARLlNG)

36:57.215 --> 36:58.507
Got it?
Yes.

36:58.633 --> 37:00.759
Here it is.
lt's very strong.

37:00.844 --> 37:01.886
Half-grain solution.

37:01.970 --> 37:03.512
Good. Now, then.

37:03.972 --> 37:05.389
You stand there.

37:05.473 --> 37:07.808
When he goes toward you,
l will make the injection
in his back.

37:07.893 --> 37:09.018
Right.

37:10.353 --> 37:11.729
Ready?
Yes.

37:14.858 --> 37:16.025
(DOOR RATTLlNG)

37:24.868 --> 37:26.035
(GROWLS)

37:36.796 --> 37:37.796
(SCREAMlNG)

37:38.214 --> 37:39.715
Get back. Back!

37:40.759 --> 37:42.009
(GROWLlNG)

37:49.517 --> 37:50.684
(GRUNTlNG)

38:01.154 --> 38:02.780
(CONFUSED GRUNTS)

38:06.368 --> 38:07.952
(KNOCKlNG ON DOOR)

38:12.540 --> 38:14.917
Dr. Waldman?
Dr. Waldman !

38:15.543 --> 38:16.627
Are you hurt?

38:16.711 --> 38:18.462
No, no, l'm all right.
lt's nothing.

38:18.713 --> 38:20.214
See who's at the door.

38:20.590 --> 38:21.882
(lNCESSANT KNOCKlNG)

38:23.760 --> 38:25.094
What's happening here?

38:25.220 --> 38:27.388
Elizabeth and your father
are coming up the hill
to see you.

38:27.472 --> 38:28.889
You must keep them out.
Too late.

38:28.974 --> 38:31.767
They must not see that.
Here, quick,
give me a hand.

38:31.935 --> 38:33.102
Quick.

38:44.072 --> 38:45.406
Down here.

38:45.865 --> 38:46.865
(GRUNTS)

38:47.784 --> 38:50.327
Henry, you better
hurry upstairs and get
that blood off your face

38:50.412 --> 38:51.745
before your father
and Elizabeth get here.

38:51.830 --> 38:52.913
All right.

39:00.922 --> 39:05.592
Well, pretty sort of place
for my son to be in,
l must say.

39:06.761 --> 39:08.595
ls that the front door?

39:08.680 --> 39:09.847
Yes, this is it.

39:09.931 --> 39:11.098
Why,

39:11.933 --> 39:15.477
l don't like it,
but here goes.

39:18.982 --> 39:20.482
Why, that. . .

39:21.026 --> 39:23.944
There doesn't seem to be
anybody in the place.

39:24.320 --> 39:25.446
Oh !

39:25.530 --> 39:26.864
(KNOCKlNG)

39:27.449 --> 39:28.490
God !

39:31.953 --> 39:33.203
(CHUCKLlNG)

39:33.288 --> 39:36.498
What a forsaken
place here.

39:36.791 --> 39:39.501
You're trying to
burn it down, eh?
What's that for, eh?

39:39.627 --> 39:41.837
What's the matter
with you?

39:41.963 --> 39:44.339
You look as though
you've been kicked
by a horse.

39:44.466 --> 39:46.091
Where's Henry?
Why. . .

39:46.176 --> 39:47.259
Well?

39:47.343 --> 39:48.677
He can't be
disturbed just now.

39:48.803 --> 39:51.805
Oh, can't he?
(SCOFFS) l'll soon
settle that nonsense.

39:52.223 --> 39:53.557
Victor, where is he?

39:53.641 --> 39:56.393
This place seems to drive
everybody crazy. l. . .

39:56.478 --> 39:58.854
Good heavens,
what's that?

39:58.980 --> 40:02.191
l beg your pardon.
l am Dr. Waldman.

40:02.317 --> 40:05.194
Oh, are you?
l'm Baron Frankenstein.

40:05.653 --> 40:08.989
Perhaps you know
what all this
tommyrot's about.

40:09.074 --> 40:11.700
(COUGHS)
l'll be shot if l do.

40:11.826 --> 40:14.203
l would advise you
to take Henry away
from here at once.

40:14.329 --> 40:17.372
What do you suppose
l'm here for, pleasure? Huh?

40:18.166 --> 40:21.043
Where are you, my dear?
Oh, there you are.

40:21.169 --> 40:23.295
Let's go and see
what's up the awful stairs.

40:23.379 --> 40:26.048
l don't know how the deuce
l'm going to get up them.

40:27.092 --> 40:29.426
Just watch me.
Do the trick.

40:29.511 --> 40:31.178
Leave them alone.

40:31.888 --> 40:34.056
No banisters
or anything else.

40:34.182 --> 40:36.016
God bless his soul.
How much further?

40:38.728 --> 40:39.937
HENRY: Come in.

40:42.690 --> 40:43.690
Henry.

40:43.775 --> 40:44.858
Elizabeth.

40:47.946 --> 40:49.113
ELlZABETH: Henry!

40:50.615 --> 40:53.075
Victor, Dr. Waldman,
come quickly!

40:54.077 --> 40:55.285
My dear, what have they
done to you?

40:55.370 --> 40:57.788
Poor, poor, Fritz.
lt's all my fault.

40:58.039 --> 41:00.582
Get him on the sofa.
Come on.

41:02.127 --> 41:04.419
Oh. Oh, my boy.

41:08.883 --> 41:10.217
Thank you.

41:10.885 --> 41:12.803
Have you got any brandy?

41:13.054 --> 41:14.346
(MOANlNG)

41:15.223 --> 41:17.891
l did it.
Quick, quick,
quick, quick.

41:20.770 --> 41:22.479
Here, l'll do that.

41:23.314 --> 41:27.067
Come on, boy.
Now, now, now,
drink. Drink this.

41:29.737 --> 41:32.156
There. There, that's better.

41:32.615 --> 41:35.284
l'm going to take you
home with me, Henry.

41:35.410 --> 41:37.452
No, l can't. My work.

41:37.912 --> 41:39.913
What will happen
to the records of
my experiment?

41:39.998 --> 41:41.290
We will preserve them.

41:41.416 --> 41:44.418
And. . .
l will see that it is
painlessly destroyed.

41:44.502 --> 41:46.962
No.
Yes, yes.
Leave it all to me.

41:47.088 --> 41:49.673
Poor Fritz. All my fault.

41:49.757 --> 41:51.967
There, Henry.
You can't do
any more now.

41:52.093 --> 41:54.803
You must come home
until you get well again.

41:54.929 --> 41:57.806
You'll soon feel better
when you get out of here.

43:16.177 --> 43:17.177
(GRUNTS)

43:18.513 --> 43:19.513
(CHOKlNG)

43:40.410 --> 43:41.660
(GROWLS)

44:08.563 --> 44:11.273
lt's like heaven,
being with you again.

44:11.607 --> 44:14.026
Heaven wasn't so far away
all the time, you know.

44:14.110 --> 44:16.903
l know,
but l didn't realize it.

44:17.947 --> 44:19.281
My work. . .

44:19.741 --> 44:21.992
Those horrible
days and nights.

44:22.952 --> 44:24.661
l couldn't think
of anything else.

44:24.746 --> 44:25.787
Henry.

44:26.247 --> 44:29.833
You're not to think
of those things anymore.
You promised.

44:30.126 --> 44:32.502
All right.
Let's think about us.

44:33.421 --> 44:34.588
When will our wedding be?

44:37.925 --> 44:39.259
Let's make it soon.

44:40.011 --> 44:41.261
As soon as you like.

44:50.605 --> 44:52.439
(BELLS RlNGlNG)
For three generations,

44:52.940 --> 44:56.526
these orange blossoms
have been worn
at our weddings.

44:57.278 --> 44:59.988
Your great-grandfather
wore this, Henry.

45:00.823 --> 45:03.700
Looks as good
as new now, eh?

45:03.785 --> 45:05.327
Thank you.
And here.

45:05.453 --> 45:08.330
Here's one
to make the best man
look still better.

45:08.456 --> 45:09.498
Thank you, sir.

45:09.582 --> 45:10.832
Thirty years ago,

45:11.459 --> 45:14.961
l placed this on your
mother's head, Henry.

45:16.172 --> 45:20.342
Today you'll make me
very happy by doing
the same for Elizabeth.

45:21.135 --> 45:24.137
And l hope
in 30 years time,

45:24.222 --> 45:27.015
a youngster of yours
will be carrying on
the tradition.

45:27.100 --> 45:28.100
(ALL CHUCKLlNG)

45:28.184 --> 45:32.145
And now, how about
a little drink, eh?
Come on.

45:33.022 --> 45:36.817
My grandfather
bought this wine
and laid it down.

45:38.319 --> 45:40.987
My grandmother
wouldn't let him drink it.

45:41.197 --> 45:44.324
Oh, bless her heart.
Here's to your
very good health.

45:45.201 --> 45:48.078
Well, you all full?
Yes? Come along.

45:48.413 --> 45:52.666
Here's a health to a son
of the house of Frankenstein.

45:52.750 --> 45:55.252
ALL: A son to the house
of Frankenstein.

45:57.046 --> 45:59.840
Here's a jolly good health
to young Frankenstein.

45:59.924 --> 46:01.675
ALL: Young Frankenstein.

46:02.677 --> 46:03.927
Here, Hyde.

46:04.846 --> 46:07.180
Give the servants
some champagne.

46:07.265 --> 46:08.682
This stuff's
wasted on them.

46:10.017 --> 46:11.935
Well, well, well, well.

46:14.856 --> 46:17.816
BARON: Go on, mop it up,
mop it up. lt'll do you good.

46:17.900 --> 46:19.276
To the house
of Frankenstein.

46:19.360 --> 46:20.735
ALL: To the house
of Frankenstein.

46:20.862 --> 46:22.070
BARON: Thank you.

46:22.530 --> 46:25.365
Now, then, now be off
about your business.

46:30.580 --> 46:31.580
(PEOPLE WHOOPlNG)

46:31.664 --> 46:33.707
BARON: Listen.
Listen to them.

46:35.376 --> 46:38.044
The boys and girls
are busy, my dear.

46:41.549 --> 46:42.883
(PEOPLE CHEERlNG)

46:46.345 --> 46:47.554
(BAND PLAYlNG)

46:51.809 --> 46:54.895
lt's extraordinary
how friendly you can
make a lot of people

46:54.979 --> 46:57.063
on a couple of
bottles of beer.

46:57.565 --> 46:59.608
Tomorrow
they'll all be fighting.

46:59.692 --> 47:00.984
No doubt.

47:02.111 --> 47:03.320
They're calling
for you, Baron.

47:03.404 --> 47:04.488
Eh, oh.

47:05.072 --> 47:06.781
Well, l suppose
l'd better show myself.

47:06.866 --> 47:07.908
WOMAN: Make a little talk.

47:08.576 --> 47:09.576
(ALL CHEERlNG)

47:13.122 --> 47:14.372
MAN: Quiet!

47:15.333 --> 47:17.542
Thank you all
very much indeed.

47:17.627 --> 47:19.794
l am very pleased
to see you all,

47:19.879 --> 47:21.505
and l hope
there's plenty of beer.

47:21.589 --> 47:23.340
At all events
there's lots more
where that came from.

47:23.424 --> 47:24.424
(ALL WHOOPlNG)

47:29.430 --> 47:31.431
(MUSlC CONTlNUES PLAYlNG)

47:59.585 --> 48:03.046
You stay here, Maria.
l'll just take a look
at my traps.

48:03.130 --> 48:06.299
Then we'll go
to the village and have
a grand time, huh?

48:07.176 --> 48:09.052
You won't be
long, Daddy?
Oh, no, no.

48:09.136 --> 48:12.097
lf Hans comes by,
tell him
l'll be back soon? Hmm?

